Package: fmbenchmark
Type: Package
Title: Benchmarking Framework for Statistical Fine-Mapping Methods
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Lucas",
           family = "Siu",
           email = "ls1020@ic.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A framework for benchmarking statistical fine-mapping methods
    using simulated genetic data. Simulates genotypes from 1000 Genomes
    Phase 3 haplotypes (via sim1000G), generates phenotypes under sparse
    or sparse+infinitesimal genetic architectures with optional functional
    annotations, applies a catalogue of fine-mapping methods (SuSiE,
    SuSiE-inf, FINEMAP, ABF, CARMA, PAINTOR, Funmap, BEATRICE, Functional
    BEATRICE, SparsePro, marginal-z baseline, and PolyFun-style oracle and
    estimated-prior variants), and evaluates them via AUPRC, credible-set
    coverage / power / size, PIP calibration, and runtime — stratified by
    causal-variant count, heritability, p_causal, causal-variant MAF, and
    annotation regime. Supports both per-locus and genome-wide simulation
    and an LD-mismatch experiment via an independent reference panel.
